@notice The (older) MasterChef contract gives out a constant number of SUSHI per Block.

 The allocation point for this pool on MCV1 is the total allocation point for all pools that receive double incentives.

documentation.text:
@dev Returns the multiplication of two signed integers, reverting on
 overflow.
 Counterpart to Solidity's `*` operator.
 Requirements:
 - Multiplication cannot overflow.

@dev Returns the integer division of two signed integers. Reverts on
 division by zero. The result is rounded towards zero.
 Counterpart to Solidity's `/` operator. Note: this function uses a
 `revert` opcode (which leaves remaining gas untouched) while Solidity
 uses an invalid opcode to revert (consuming all remaining gas).
 Requirements:
 - The divisor cannot be zero.

@dev Returns the subtraction of two signed integers, reverting on
 overflow.
 Counterpart to Solidity's `-` operator.
 Requirements:
 - Subtraction cannot overflow.

@dev Returns the addition of two signed integers, reverting on
 overflow.
 Counterpart to Solidity's `+` operator.
 Requirements:
 - Addition cannot overflow.

list-detectors.title: Storage abiencoderv2 array
list-detectors.description: `solc` versions `0.4.7`-`0.5.10` contain a [compiler bug](https://blog.ethereum.org/2019/06/25/solidity-storage-array-bugs.) leading to incorrect ABI encoder usage.
list-detectors.recommendation: Use a compiler >= `0.5.10`.

list-detectors.title: Modifying storage array by value
list-detectors.description: Detect arrays passed to a function that expects reference to a storage array
list-detectors.recommendation: Ensure the correct usage of `memory` and `storage` in the function parameters. Make all the locations explicit.

list-detectors.title: The order of parameters in a shift instruction is incorrect.
list-detectors.description: Detect if the values in a shift operation are reversed
list-detectors.recommendation: Swap the order of parameters.

list-detectors.title: Multiple constructor schemes
list-detectors.description: Detect multiple constructor definitions in the same contract (using new and old schemes).
list-detectors.recommendation: Only declare one constructor, preferably using the new scheme `constructor(...)` instead of `function <contractName>(...)`.

list-detectors.title: Contract's name reused
list-detectors.description:
If a codebase has two contracts the similar names, the compilation artifacts
will not contain one of the contracts with the duplicate name.
list-detectors.exploit_scenario:
Bob's `truffle` codebase has two contracts named `ERC20`.
When `truffle compile` runs, only one of the two contracts will generate artifacts in `build/contracts`.
As a result, the second contract cannot be analyzed.
list-detectors.recommendation: Rename the contract.

list-detectors.title: Public mappings with nested variables
list-detectors.description: Prior to Solidity 0.5, a public mapping with nested structures returned [incorrect values](https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/issues/5520).
list-detectors.exploit_scenario: Bob interacts with a contract that has a public mapping with nested structures. The values returned by the mapping are incorrect, breaking Bob's usage
list-detectors.recommendation: Do not use public mapping with nested structures.

list-detectors.title: Right-To-Left-Override control character is used
list-detectors.description: An attacker can manipulate the logic of the contract by using a right-to-left-override character (`U+202E)`.
list-detectors.recommendation: Special control characters must not be allowed.

list-detectors.title: State variables shadowing
list-detectors.description: Detection of state variables shadowed.
list-detectors.recommendation: Remove the state variable shadowing.

list-detectors.title: Functions allowing anyone to destruct the contract
list-detectors.description: Unprotected call to a function executing `selfdestruct`/`suicide`.
list-detectors.recommendation: Protect access to all sensitive functions.

list-detectors.title: Uninitialized state variables
list-detectors.description: Uninitialized state variables.
list-detectors.recommendation: Initialize all the variables. If a variable is meant to be initialized to zero, explicitly set it to zero.

list-detectors.title: Uninitialized storage variables
list-detectors.description: An uninitialized storage variable will act as a reference to the first state variable, and can override a critical variable.
list-detectors.recommendation: Initialize all storage variables.

list-detectors.title: Unprotected upgradeable contract
list-detectors.description: Detects logic contract that can be destructed.
list-detectors.recommendation: Add a constructor to ensure `initialize` cannot be called on the logic contract.

list-detectors.title: Functions that send Ether to arbitrary destinations
list-detectors.description: Unprotected call to a function sending Ether to an arbitrary address.
list-detectors.recommendation: Ensure that an arbitrary user cannot withdraw unauthorized funds.

list-detectors.title: Tainted array length assignment
list-detectors.description: Detects the direct assignment of an array's length.
list-detectors.recommendation:
Do not allow array lengths to be set directly set; instead, opt to add values as needed.
Otherwise, thoroughly review the contract to ensure a user-controlled variable cannot reach an array length assignment.

list-detectors.title: Controlled delegatecall destination
list-detectors.description: `Delegatecall` or `callcode` to an address controlled by the user.
list-detectors.recommendation: Avoid using `delegatecall`. Use only trusted destinations.

list-detectors.title: Reentrancy vulnerabilities (theft of ethers)
list-detectors.description:
Detection of the [reentrancy bug](https://github.com/trailofbits/not-so-smart-contracts/tree/master/reentrancy).
Do not report reentrancies that don't involve Ether (see `reentrancy-no-eth`)
list-detectors.recommendation: Apply the [`check-effects-interactions pattern`](http://solidity.readthedocs.io/en/v0.4.21/security-considerations.html#re-entrancy).

list-detectors.title: Signed storage integer array compiler bug
list-detectors.description:
`solc` versions `0.4.7`-`0.5.10` contain [a compiler bug](https://blog.ethereum.org/2019/06/25/solidity-storage-array-bugs)
leading to incorrect values in signed integer arrays.
list-detectors.recommendation: Use a compiler version >= `0.5.10`.

list-detectors.title: Weak PRNG
list-detectors.description: Weak PRNG due to a modulo on `block.timestamp`, `now` or `blockhash`. These can be influenced by miners to some extent so they should be avoided.
list-detectors.recommendation: Do not use `block.timestamp`, `now` or `blockhash` as a source of randomness

list-detectors.title: Detect dangerous enum conversion
list-detectors.description: Detect out-of-range `enum` conversion (`solc` < `0.4.5`).
list-detectors.recommendation: Use a recent compiler version. If `solc` <`0.4.5` is required, check the `enum` conversion range.

list-detectors.title: Incorrect ERC20 interfaces
list-detectors.description: Incorrect return values for `ERC20` functions. A contract compiled with Solidity > 0.4.22 interacting with these functions will fail to execute them, as the return value is missing.
list-detectors.recommendation: Set the appropriate return values and types for the defined `ERC20` functions.

list-detectors.title: Incorrect ERC721 interfaces
list-detectors.description: Incorrect return values for `ERC721` functions. A contract compiled with solidity > 0.4.22 interacting with these functions will fail to execute them, as the return value is missing.
list-detectors.recommendation: Set the appropriate return values and vtypes for the defined `ERC721` functions.

list-detectors.title: Dangerous strict equalities
list-detectors.description: Use of strict equalities that can be easily manipulated by an attacker.
list-detectors.recommendation: Don't use strict equality to determine if an account has enough Ether or tokens.

list-detectors.title: Contracts that lock ether
list-detectors.description: Contract with a `payable` function, but without a withdrawal capacity.
list-detectors.recommendation: Remove the payable attribute or add a withdraw function.

list-detectors.title: Deletion on mapping containing a structure
list-detectors.description: A deletion in a structure containing a mapping will not delete the mapping (see the [Solidity documentation](https://solidity.readthedocs.io/en/latest/types.html##delete)). The remaining data may be used to compromise the contract.
list-detectors.recommendation: Use a lock mechanism instead of a deletion to disable structure containing a mapping.

list-detectors.title: State variables shadowing from abstract contracts
list-detectors.description: Detection of state variables shadowed from abstract contracts.
list-detectors.recommendation: Remove the state variable shadowing.

list-detectors.title: Tautology or contradiction
list-detectors.description: Detects expressions that are tautologies or contradictions.
list-detectors.recommendation: Fix the incorrect comparison by changing the value type or the comparison.

list-detectors.title: Misuse of Boolean constant
list-detectors.description: Detects the misuse of a Boolean constant.
list-detectors.recommendation: Verify and simplify the condition.

list-detectors.title: Constant functions using assembly code
list-detectors.description:
Functions declared as `constant`/`pure`/`view` using assembly code.

`constant`/`pure`/`view` was not enforced prior to Solidity 0.5.
Starting from Solidity 0.5, a call to a `constant`/`pure`/`view` function uses the `STATICCALL` opcode, which reverts in case of state modification.

As a result, a call to an [incorrectly labeled function may trap a contract compiled with Solidity 0.5](https://solidity.readthedocs.io/en/develop/050-breaking-changes.html#interoperability-with-older-contracts).
list-detectors.recommendation: Ensure the attributes of contracts compiled prior to Solidity 0.5.0 are correct.

list-detectors.title: Constant functions changing the state
list-detectors.description:
Functions declared as `constant`/`pure`/`view` change the state.

`constant`/`pure`/`view` was not enforced prior to Solidity 0.5.
Starting from Solidity 0.5, a call to a `constant`/`pure`/`view` function uses the `STATICCALL` opcode, which reverts in case of state modification.

As a result, a call to an [incorrectly labeled function may trap a contract compiled with Solidity 0.5](https://solidity.readthedocs.io/en/develop/050-breaking-changes.html#interoperability-with-older-contracts).
list-detectors.recommendation: Ensure that attributes of contracts compiled prior to Solidity 0.5.0 are correct.

list-detectors.title: Imprecise arithmetic operations order
list-detectors.description: Solidity integer division might truncate. As a result, performing multiplication before division can sometimes avoid loss of precision.
list-detectors.recommendation: Consider ordering multiplication before division.

list-detectors.title: Reentrancy vulnerabilities (no theft of ethers)
list-detectors.description:
Detection of the [reentrancy bug](https://github.com/trailofbits/not-so-smart-contracts/tree/master/reentrancy).
Do not report reentrancies that involve Ether (see `reentrancy-eth`).
list-detectors.recommendation: Apply the [`check-effects-interactions` pattern](http://solidity.readthedocs.io/en/v0.4.21/security-considerations.html#re-entrancy).

list-detectors.title: Reused base constructor
list-detectors.description: Detects if the same base constructor is called with arguments from two different locations in the same inheritance hierarchy.
list-detectors.recommendation: Remove the duplicate constructor call.

list-detectors.title: Dangerous usage of `tx.origin`
list-detectors.description: `tx.origin`-based protection can be abused by a malicious contract if a legitimate user interacts with the malicious contract.
list-detectors.recommendation: Do not use `tx.origin` for authorization.

list-detectors.title: Unchecked low-level calls
list-detectors.description: The return value of a low-level call is not checked.
list-detectors.recommendation: Ensure that the return value of a low-level call is checked or logged.

list-detectors.title: Unchecked send
list-detectors.description: The return value of a `send` is not checked.
list-detectors.recommendation: Ensure that the return value of `send` is checked or logged.

list-detectors.title: Uninitialized local variables
list-detectors.description: Uninitialized local variables.
list-detectors.recommendation: Initialize all the variables. If a variable is meant to be initialized to zero, explicitly set it to zero.

list-detectors.title: Unused return values
list-detectors.description: The return value of an external call is not stored in a local or state variable.
list-detectors.recommendation: Ensure that all the return values of the function calls are used.

list-detectors.title: Modifiers that can return the default value
list-detectors.description: If a modifier does not execute `_` or revert, the execution of the function will return the default value, which can be misleading for the caller.
list-detectors.recommendation: All the paths in a modifier must execute `_` or revert.

list-detectors.title: Built-in symbol shadowing
list-detectors.description: Detection of shadowing built-in symbols using local variables, state variables, functions, modifiers, or events.
list-detectors.recommendation: Rename the local variables, state variables, functions, modifiers, and events that shadow a builtin symbol.

list-detectors.title: Local variables shadowing
list-detectors.description: Detection of shadowing using local variables.
list-detectors.recommendation: Rename the local variables that shadow another component.

list-detectors.title: Uninitialized function pointer calls in constructors
list-detectors.description: solc versions `0.4.5`-`0.4.26` and `0.5.0`-`0.5.8` contain a compiler bug leading to unexpected behavior when calling uninitialized function pointers in constructors.
list-detectors.recommendation: Initialize function pointers before calling. Avoid function pointers if possible.

list-detectors.title: Local variables used prior their declaration
list-detectors.description: Detects the possible usage of a variable before the declaration is stepped over (either because it is later declared, or declared in another scope).
list-detectors.recommendation: Move all variable declarations prior to any usage of the variable, and ensure that reaching a variable declaration does not depend on some conditional if it is used unconditionally.

list-detectors.title: Constructor called not implemented
list-detectors.description: Detect the call to a constructor that is not implemented
list-detectors.recommendation: Remove the constructor call.

list-detectors.title: Multiple calls in a loop
list-detectors.description: Calls inside a loop might lead to a denial-of-service attack.
list-detectors.recommendation: Favor [pull over push](https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/wiki/Safety#favor-pull-over-push-for-external-calls) strategy for external calls.

list-detectors.title: Missing Events Access Control
list-detectors.description: Detect missing events for critical access control parameters
list-detectors.recommendation: Emit an event for critical parameter changes.

list-detectors.title: Missing Events Arithmetic
list-detectors.description: Detect missing events for critical arithmetic parameters.
list-detectors.recommendation: Emit an event for critical parameter changes.

list-detectors.title: Dangerous unary expressions
list-detectors.description: Unary expressions such as `x=+1` probably typos.
list-detectors.recommendation: Remove the unary expression.

list-detectors.title: Missing Zero Address Validation
list-detectors.description: Detect missing zero address validation.
list-detectors.recommendation: Check that the address is not zero.

list-detectors.title: Benign reentrancy vulnerabilities
list-detectors.description:
Detection of the [reentrancy bug](https://github.com/trailofbits/not-so-smart-contracts/tree/master/reentrancy).
Only report reentrancy that acts as a double call (see `reentrancy-eth`, `reentrancy-no-eth`).
list-detectors.recommendation: Apply the [`check-effects-interactions` pattern](http://solidity.readthedocs.io/en/v0.4.21/security-considerations.html#re-entrancy).

list-detectors.title: Reentrancy vulnerabilities leading to out-of-order Events
list-detectors.description:
Detection of the [reentrancy bug](https://github.com/trailofbits/not-so-smart-contracts/tree/master/reentrancy).
Only report reentrancies leading to out-of-order events.
list-detectors.recommendation: Apply the [`check-effects-interactions` pattern](http://solidity.readthedocs.io/en/v0.4.21/security-considerations.html#re-entrancy).

list-detectors.title: Dangerous usage of `block.timestamp`
list-detectors.description: Dangerous usage of `block.timestamp`. `block.timestamp` can be manipulated by miners.
list-detectors.exploit_scenario: "Bob's contract relies on `block.timestamp` for its randomness. Eve is a miner and manipulates `block.timestamp` to exploit Bob's contract.
list-detectors.recommendation: Avoid relying on `block.timestamp`.

list-detectors.title: Assembly usage
list-detectors.description: The use of assembly is error-prone and should be avoided.
list-detectors.recommendation: Do not use `evm` assembly.

list-detectors.title: Assert state change
list-detectors.description: Incorrect use of `assert()`. See Solidity best [practices](https://solidity.readthedocs.io/en/latest/control-structures.html#id4).
list-detectors.recommendation: Use `require` for invariants modifying the state.

list-detectors.title: Comparison to boolean constant
list-detectors.description: Detects the comparison to boolean constants.
list-detectors.recommendation: Remove the equality to the boolean constant.

list-detectors.title: Deprecated Solidity Standards
list-detectors.description: Detect the usage of deprecated standards.
list-detectors.recommendation: Replace all uses of deprecated symbols.

list-detectors.title: Un-indexed ERC20 event parameters
list-detectors.description: Detects whether events defined by the `ERC20` specification that should have some parameters as `indexed` are missing the `indexed` keyword.
list-detectors.recommendation: Add the `indexed` keyword to event parameters that should include it, according to the `ERC20` specification.

list-detectors.title: Function initializing state variables
list-detectors.description: Detects the immediate initialization of state variables through function calls that are not pure/constant, or that use non-constant state variable.
list-detectors.recommendation: Remove any initialization of state variables via non-constant state variables or function calls. If variables must be set upon contract deployment, locate initialization in the constructor instead.

list-detectors.title: Low level calls
list-detectors.description: The use of low-level calls is error-prone. Low-level calls do not check for [code existence](https://solidity.readthedocs.io/en/v0.4.25/control-structures.html#error-handling-assert-require-revert-and-exceptions) or call success.
list-detectors.recommendation: Avoid low-level calls. Check the call success. If the call is meant for a contract, check for code existence.

list-detectors.title: Missing inheritance
list-detectors.description: Detect missing inheritance.
list-detectors.recommendation: Inherit from the missing interface or contract.

list-detectors.title: Conformity to Solidity naming conventions
list-detectors.description:
Solidity defines a [naming convention](https://solidity.readthedocs.io/en/v0.4.25/style-guide.html#naming-conventions) that should be followed.
#### Rule exceptions
- Allow constant variable name/symbol/decimals to be lowercase (`ERC20`).
- Allow `_` at the beginning of the `mixed_case` match for private variables and unused parameters.
list-detectors.recommendation: Follow the Solidity [naming convention](https://solidity.readthedocs.io/en/v0.4.25/style-guide.html#naming-conventions).

list-detectors.title: If different pragma directives are used
list-detectors.description: Detect whether different Solidity versions are used.
list-detectors.recommendation: Use one Solidity version.

list-detectors.title: Redundant statements
list-detectors.description: Detect the usage of redundant statements that have no effect.
list-detectors.recommendation: Remove redundant statements if they congest code but offer no value.

list-detectors.title: Incorrect Solidity version
list-detectors.description:
`solc` frequently releases new compiler versions. Using an old version prevents access to new Solidity security checks.
We also recommend avoiding complex `pragma` statement.
list-detectors.recommendation:
Deploy with any of the following Solidity versions:
- 0.5.11 - 0.5.13,
- 0.5.15 - 0.5.17,
- 0.6.8,
- 0.6.10 - 0.6.11.
Use a simple pragma version that allows any of these versions.
Consider using the latest version of Solidity for testing.

list-detectors.title: Unimplemented functions
list-detectors.description: Detect functions that are not implemented on derived-most contracts.
list-detectors.recommendation: Implement all unimplemented functions in any contract you intend to use directly (not simply inherit from).

list-detectors.title: Unused state variables
list-detectors.description: Unused state variable.
list-detectors.recommendation: Remove unused state variables.

list-detectors.title: Costly operations in a loop
list-detectors.description: Costly operations inside a loop might waste gas, so optimizations are justified.
list-detectors.recommendation: Use a local variable to hold the loop computation result.

list-detectors.title: Reentrancy vulnerabilities through send and transfer
list-detectors.description:
Detection of the [reentrancy bug](https://github.com/trailofbits/not-so-smart-contracts/tree/master/reentrancy).
Only report reentrancy that is based on `transfer` or `send`.
list-detectors.recommendation: Apply the [`check-effects-interactions` pattern](http://solidity.readthedocs.io/en/v0.4.21/security-considerations.html#re-entrancy).

list-detectors.title: Variable names are too similar
list-detectors.description: Detect variables with names that are too similar.
list-detectors.exploit_scenario: Bob uses several variables with similar names. As a result, his code is difficult to review.
list-detectors.recommendation: Prevent variables from having similar names.

list-detectors.title: Conformance to numeric notation best practices
list-detectors.description: Literals with many digits are difficult to read and review.
list-detectors.recommendation:
Use:
- [Ether suffix](https://solidity.readthedocs.io/en/latest/units-and-global-variables.html#ether-units),
- [Time suffix](https://solidity.readthedocs.io/en/latest/units-and-global-variables.html#time-units), or
- [The scientific notation](https://solidity.readthedocs.io/en/latest/types.html#rational-and-integer-literals)

list-detectors.title: State variables that could be declared constant
list-detectors.description: Constant state variables should be declared constant to save gas.
list-detectors.recommendation: Add the `constant` attributes to state variables that never change.

list-detectors.title: Public function that could be declared external
list-detectors.description: `public` functions that are never called by the contract should be declared `external` to save gas.
list-detectors.recommendation: Use the `external` attribute for functions never called from the contract.
